<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-08-01T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-08-01T17:00:00-05:00" n="351" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d351">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00112 European War 1939/3098:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Leahy</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-08-01T18:00:00-04:00">August
                                        1, 1941—6 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>616. Your 957, July 29, 9 p.m. Should you be approached in connection
                                with the possibility of Murphy visiting Vichy, you may reply that
                                you have been informed by the Department that the present status of
                                the arrangement as regards North Africa will necessitate his
                                continued presence there for the time being. It is felt that he will
                                be needed there to continue to supervise the operation of this
                                agreement.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>